1:
Listen to my call to you, Yahweh;
\q think about my groanings.
\q

4:
Certainly you are not a God who approves of evil;
\q evil people will not be your guests.
\q

5:
The arrogant will not stand in your presence;
\q you hate all who behave wickedly.
\q

7:
But as for me, because of your great covenant faithfulness, I will come into your house;
\q in reverence I will bow down toward your holy temple.
\q

9:
For there is no truth in their mouth;
\q their inward being is wicked;
\q their throat is an open tomb;
\q they flatter with their tongue.
\q

11:
But may all those who take refuge in you rejoice;
\q let them always shout for joy because you defend them;
\q let them be joyful in you, those who love your name.
\q
